Version 2.1.0-dev.20160905

Given:

``` ts
    enum Foo { Bar }

    type Baz = {
        type: Foo.Bar
    }

    const baz: Baz = { type: Foo.Bar };
```

When I rename `Foo.Bar` on line one, it only renames usages of the enum as a value, not as a type.

Expected result (rename to Bob)

``` ts
    enum Foo { Bob }

    type Baz = {
        type: Foo.Bob
    }

    const baz: Baz = { type: Foo.Bob };
```

Actual result

``` ts
    enum Foo { Bob }

    type Baz = {
        type: Foo.Bar
    }

    const baz: Baz = { type: Foo.Bob };
```

